436
00:27:40,664 --> 00:27:43,051
Actually, I'm depressed.

437
00:27:43,384 --> 00:27:44,344
Why?

438
00:27:44,891 --> 00:27:47,531
A woman threatens me if I don't marry her.

439
00:27:48,479 --> 00:27:52,646
Okay, okay.
The woman with the long hair outside the movie theater the other night?

440
00:27:53,938 --> 00:27:56,464
Yes. She's a woman named Asako from a supply store on Miyuki Rd.

441
00:27:56,755 --> 00:27:59,828
I'm tired of it, and she keeps trying to scare me.

442
00:28:00,618 --> 00:28:02,258
You didn't handle her?

443
00:28:02,584 --> 00:28:03,444
Yeah..

444
00:28:03,664 --> 00:28:05,284
That's bad.

445
00:28:06,717 --> 00:28:08,517
Have a seat.

446
00:28:12,589 --> 00:28:14,829
Hey, you don't have to worry.

447
00:28:15,476 --> 00:28:19,309
Women often say they're going to die. It's just a threat.

448
00:28:19,897 --> 00:28:21,790
But she is serious.

449
00:28:22,437 --> 00:28:27,557
Don't think too much.
No one fall in love a man like you.

450
00:28:30,883 --> 00:28:32,716
I feel a little better now.

451
00:28:37,985 --> 00:28:39,651
Don't do that.

452
00:28:40,705 --> 00:28:42,158
We're such weird friends.

453
00:28:42,485 --> 00:28:43,318
Why?

454
00:28:43,857 --> 00:28:46,750
When I see you, I have this habit of confiding in you about everything.

455
00:28:47,658 --> 00:28:49,518
I feel something weird.

456
00:28:50,257 --> 00:28:51,084
Something tells me.

457
00:28:51,232 --> 00:28:53,092
Don't think too much.

458
00:28:53,799 --> 00:28:55,599
We're just normal friend.

459
00:28:55,658 --> 00:28:59,511
But we're lying about something.

460
00:29:00,647 --> 00:29:03,621
Everything you've said has been a lie?

461
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:06,647
It could be.

462
00:29:13,951 --> 00:29:16,491
You are kind of weird today.

463
00:29:17,125 --> 00:29:19,638
Don't think too much.

464
00:29:20,298 --> 00:29:22,145
