527
00:32:34,114 --> 00:32:35,194
I don't wanna meet her.

528
00:32:35,294 --> 00:32:37,000
It can't be helped.

529
00:32:37,180 --> 00:32:38,794
I'm checking her.

530
00:32:40,348 --> 00:32:41,374
Welcome.

531
00:32:42,474 --> 00:32:44,054
Looking for a gift?

532
00:32:45,161 --> 00:32:45,954
For your dad?

533
00:32:46,251 --> 00:32:46,758
No.

534
00:32:47,065 --> 00:32:48,898
For young man.

535
00:32:51,759 --> 00:32:52,959
How about this?

536
00:32:56,332 --> 00:32:57,185
How about this?

537
00:33:08,248 --> 00:33:09,801
I bought Maki a present.

538
00:33:09,992 --> 00:33:11,098
Was she?

539
00:33:11,292 --> 00:33:16,091
She's nice.I asked her who you were, just in case.
Would you like to meet her?

540
00:33:16,359 --> 00:33:17,546
I don't wanna meet her.

541
00:33:18,446 --> 00:33:21,219
I just called and arranged to meet Kei-chan.

542
00:33:22,310 --> 00:33:25,177
It was good you didn't meet her.

543
00:33:27,076 --> 00:33:27,976
Yeah.

544
00:33:29,169 --> 00:33:29,989
You think so?

545
00:33:30,642 --> 00:33:31,342
Yeah.

546
00:33:31,925 --> 00:33:35,392
You got a better idea that your dad wouldn't have to investigate me?

547
00:33:35,667 --> 00:33:37,453
Cartoonishly good idea.

548
00:33:37,602 --> 00:33:39,442
I haven't got it.

549
00:33:39,855 --> 00:33:41,455
He's giving me a headache.

550
00:33:42,133 --> 00:33:45,080
I leave it to you.

551
00:33:46,379 --> 00:33:49,993
Why don't you have him look into Kei-chan, and maybe He won't find out.

552
00:33:51,195 --> 00:33:53,935
I don't think so.
He often calls our office.

553
00:33:54,048 --> 00:33:54,695
I see.

554
00:33:54,981 --> 00:33:57,314
I won't give my father time to check Kei-chan out.

555
00:33:57,732 --> 00:33:59,478
Well, we'll ask him permission on the spot.

556
00:34:00,435 --> 00:34:04,808
Ok let's get started!

557
00:34:04,852 --> 00:34:06,246
You're too simple.

558
00:34:18,136 --> 00:34:20,342
I went to shopping.

559
00:34:20,889 --> 00:34:22,556
Be more polite.

560
00:34:23,454 --> 00:34:26,908
Didn't Kasumi say something about stopping somewhere today?

561
00:34:27,107 --> 00:34:29,347
Yes, she said she was going to visit her brother.

562
00:34:29,567 --> 00:34:30,154
I see.

563
00:34:31,413 --> 00:34:32,380
To Asamichi.

564
00:34:39,111 --> 00:34:40,151
Hello?

565
00:34:50,905 --> 00:34:51,832
Are you Kasumi?

566
00:34:52,802 --> 00:34:54,749
Welcome.
It's unusual you visit us.

567
00:34:54,924 --> 00:34:55,891
I happened to come here.

568
00:34:56,164 --> 00:34:58,951
Anyway thanks for coming.

569
00:35:00,557 --> 00:35:02,257
Come on in, we have just the cake for you.
You want coffee?

570
00:35:02,290 --> 00:35:03,230
I'll have tea.

571
00:35:03,521 --> 00:35:04,727
I'll heat some water.

572
00:35:07,664 --> 00:35:08,871
I'll answer.

573
00:35:10,011 --> 00:35:10,824
Hello?

574
00:35:11,279 --> 00:35:13,379
Hey, Kasumi. I didn't know you were there.

575
00:35:15,382 --> 00:35:17,522
I knew you'd be there.

576
00:35:19,374 --> 00:35:23,894
I just wanted you to leave early before it gets too late.

577
00:35:26,222 --> 00:35:27,889
Say hello to Akiko.

578
00:35:30,326 --> 00:35:32,080
I guess I was wrong.

579
00:35:38,075 --> 00:35:39,588
Oh you.

580
00:35:40,062 --> 00:35:40,802
What can I do for you?

581
00:35:42,105 --> 00:35:43,305
Sawai is coming here?

582
00:35:44,011 --> 00:35:45,945
I'll get ready..

583
00:35:48,320 --> 00:35:50,060
I agree.

584
00:35:51,020 --> 00:35:51,607
Really?

585
00:35:53,248 --> 00:35:58,095
I knew Sawai well when he worked with me.
I'm sure he's perfect for you.

586
00:35:59,124 --> 00:36:00,738
Thank you, sister.

587
00:36:00,791 --> 00:36:04,124
I was thinking maybe it was.

588
00:36:05,235 --> 00:36:05,788
Why?

589
00:36:06,130 --> 00:36:08,876
I met him at birthday party.
I know exactly what you mean.

590
00:36:09,286 --> 00:36:11,766
So you guys have figured it out by now?

591
00:36:12,446 --> 00:36:13,160
Just me.

592
00:36:14,227 --> 00:36:15,333
Our family don't know about it.

593
00:36:15,820 --> 00:36:16,667
I'm relieved.

594
00:36:17,447 --> 00:36:18,920
Have a eat.

595
00:36:21,842 --> 00:36:26,509
If our family disagrees, will you support us?

596
00:36:26,868 --> 00:36:28,001
Of course I would.

597
00:36:28,174 --> 00:36:29,874
Please.

598
00:36:31,374 --> 00:36:32,914
I'm on your side.

599
00:36:37,503 --> 00:36:39,430
Why he suddenly is coming.

600
00:36:39,536 --> 00:36:41,536
He might be visiting for asking money.

601
00:36:42,170 --> 00:36:43,076
I'm home.

602
00:36:43,303 --> 00:36:44,023
Welcome back.

603
00:36:44,649 --> 00:36:45,655
No way.

604
00:36:47,329 --> 00:36:51,122
Maybe he should ask my husband to play matchmaker.

605
00:36:51,354 --> 00:36:56,276
It would make sense to bring the fiancée along.

606
00:36:59,409 --> 00:37:00,283
He's here.

607
00:37:02,242 --> 00:37:04,275
Please answer.

608
00:37:12,718 --> 00:37:13,872
Welcome back.

609
00:37:15,365 --> 00:37:16,238
Welcome.

610
00:37:16,532 --> 00:37:17,438
Excuse me.

611
00:37:19,912 --> 00:37:20,846
Come in.

612
00:37:22,086 --> 00:37:24,319
Wait in the room.

613
00:37:24,499 --> 00:37:26,039
Serve him a beer.

614
00:37:39,653 --> 00:37:40,806
I wanna kiss you.

615
00:37:43,127 --> 00:37:44,527
Please don't worry.

616
00:37:50,335 --> 00:37:51,795
You're so cute, I could eat you.

617
00:37:51,975 --> 00:37:53,963
You have to be serious.

618
00:37:55,692 --> 00:37:56,945
It's cold, isn't it?

619
00:37:57,025 --> 00:37:58,092
Welcome.

620
00:38:02,035 --> 00:38:05,862
He says he has something important to discuss with me.
Please get out.

621
00:38:18,416 --> 00:38:19,642
What do you mean?

622
00:38:19,796 --> 00:38:21,449
Well...

623
00:38:24,219 --> 00:38:25,792
I'd like to have your daughter.

624
00:38:27,146 --> 00:38:29,252
What are you talking about?

625
00:38:30,300 --> 00:38:31,727
What happened?

626
00:38:40,551 --> 00:38:42,678
He's here to borrow some money.

627
00:38:45,290 --> 00:38:47,843
Serve him another beer.

628
00:38:55,770 --> 00:39:00,364
I see what you mean.

629
00:39:01,809 --> 00:39:06,782
I'll have to discuss these issues with my wife.
Wait a minute, please.

630
00:39:07,469 --> 00:39:08,722
Excuse me.

631
00:39:21,206 --> 00:39:22,319
He's here to borrow some money?

632
00:39:22,786 --> 00:39:24,152
No at all.

633
00:39:25,962 --> 00:39:29,549
I'm sure he'll come back and investigate about you and get back to you.

634
00:39:29,846 --> 00:39:32,352
Don't worry.
But I worry.

635
00:39:32,592 --> 00:39:34,919
You're a jerk.
That doesn't make me feel any safer.

636
00:39:37,885 --> 00:39:39,885
I'll drink this if I have to.

637
00:39:40,191 --> 00:39:41,038
Are you dying?

638
00:39:41,589 --> 00:39:43,036
Don't tell anyone, but it's got sugar in it.

639
00:39:43,249 --> 00:39:44,329
You can't deceive him.

640
00:39:45,088 --> 00:39:46,708
But he's late.

641
00:39:47,381 --> 00:39:48,934
I'll go to see him.

642
00:40:04,867 --> 00:40:09,380
I had my staff check it out, and here's Sawai-kun and Maki-kun's report.
Take a look.

643
00:40:18,064 --> 00:40:18,711
Really?

644
00:40:19,124 --> 00:40:20,991
We have no chance.

645
00:40:22,756 --> 00:40:26,423
I don't have a choice in the matter, and I don't care if it's a act,
I'll take sugar or whatever.

646
00:40:44,429 --> 00:40:49,009
You're such a bad girl.
You never tell me anything.

647
00:40:49,361 --> 00:40:52,128
I'm so glad.

648
00:40:56,409 --> 00:41:00,202
Let's have party.
Prepare the food.

649
00:41:00,227 --> 00:41:01,246
I'll get it.

650
00:41:01,544 --> 00:41:02,324
Kasumi.

651
00:41:03,324 --> 00:41:04,244
Yes.

652
00:41:07,871 --> 00:41:10,531
You have good eyes for men.

653
00:41:11,037 --> 00:41:14,890
Of the three, your father and I trusted Maki the most.

654
00:41:15,331 --> 00:41:19,431
Your father just showed me the report about him.

655
00:41:19,815 --> 00:41:23,121
Sawai is super good.

656
00:41:23,540 --> 00:41:24,920
Keep eye on the food.

657
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:29,800
His relationships with women are spotless.
And he's got 150000 yen in the bank at such a young age.

658
00:41:31,481 --> 00:41:33,928
The report is so nice.

659
00:41:51,409 --> 00:41:52,549
Here.

660
00:41:53,549 --> 00:41:54,863
Let's have a seat.

661
00:42:00,690 --> 00:42:02,423
It's a nice view.

662
00:42:02,943 --> 00:42:06,450
Is it?
It's too dark for me.

663
00:42:06,965 --> 00:42:08,678
We're such weird friends.

664
00:42:09,005 --> 00:42:09,625
Why?

665
00:42:10,198 --> 00:42:14,058
When I see you, I have this habit of confiding in you about everything.

666
00:42:14,142 --> 00:42:16,296
I feel something weird.

667
00:42:16,666 --> 00:42:18,873
Don't think too much.

668
00:42:18,900 --> 00:42:22,840
But we're lying about something.

669
00:42:25,580 --> 00:42:27,580
You are kind of weird today.

670
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:28,747
You think so?

671
00:42:29,117 --> 00:42:31,897
I'm going to be weird too.

672
00:42:32,045 --> 00:42:33,445
I'm going to be weird too.

673
00:42:33,627 --> 00:42:34,247
Maki.

674
00:42:34,420 --> 00:42:35,160
Chieko.

675
00:42:42,861 --> 00:42:45,121
I have to cook Okonomiyaki.

676
00:42:49,793 --> 00:42:51,746
So, what about the wedding?

677
00:42:52,060 --> 00:42:54,620
I don't care if it's tonight or anytime soon.

678
00:42:54,879 --> 00:42:56,353
Don't rush.

679
00:42:56,378 --> 00:43:00,772
Maybe sooner would be better.

680
00:43:01,582 --> 00:43:04,528
I can't wait long.

681
00:43:04,603 --> 00:43:07,823
What about college, you got a year left?

682
00:43:08,089 --> 00:43:09,056
I could quit.

683
00:43:09,473 --> 00:43:11,319
She's proactive.

684
00:43:11,793 --> 00:43:13,286
Have a eat.

685
00:43:13,945 --> 00:43:26,601
Maki has already been living with a woman at a bar in Ginza for a year and and they have continued their de facto marital relationship.

686
00:43:27,209 --> 00:43:30,689
He's a dreadful man.

687
00:44:22,255 --> 00:44:26,942
You'll see me when you're married to her.

688
00:44:31,693 --> 00:44:33,760
I like younger women like you.

689
00:44:34,181 --> 00:44:36,455
I don't like a girl over 20.

690
00:44:44,991 --> 00:44:46,944
I'll never leave from you.

691
00:44:47,847 --> 00:44:52,187
If you marry someone behind my back, I'll kill you or I'll die.

692
00:45:22,279 --> 00:45:22,973
Kei-chan.

693
00:45:31,882 --> 00:45:33,569
Oh you.

694
00:45:34,270 --> 00:45:38,297
Please treat me nice.

695
00:45:39,031 --> 00:45:42,144
You won't wake up.

696
00:45:45,270 --> 00:45:49,457
From now on, don't ever cheat on me.

697
00:45:50,535 --> 00:45:51,754
I know.

698
00:45:54,614 --> 00:45:55,481
You smell good.

699
00:45:57,821 --> 00:45:59,719
How about you take a bath?

700
00:46:00,407 --> 00:46:01,868
And after we eat, we'll go for a walk.

701
00:46:02,968 --> 00:46:05,047
You are naked.

702
00:46:06,414 --> 00:46:09,445
Don't look at me.

703
00:46:15,586 --> 00:46:18,235
Oh Ochiyo?

704
00:46:18,414 --> 00:46:20,813
Good morning.
I thought you were still sleeping.

705
00:46:22,727 --> 00:46:24,578
Because...

706
00:46:25,180 --> 00:46:27,078
Was he nice to you this morning?

707
00:46:29,461 --> 00:46:32,922
Very.
I wasn't afraid of him.

708
00:46:34,203 --> 00:46:37,094
No, I don't know.
No, you don't.

709
00:46:37,797 --> 00:46:40,672
What's wrong?
What did Kei-chan? do to you?

710
00:46:44,313 --> 00:46:47,250
Don't provoke me, it'll make me sad.

711
00:46:49,974 --> 00:46:52,482
I have to go.
I wish you all the best.

712
00:47:04,823 --> 00:47:08,612
Maki?
I'm sorry. Secretary, Maki please.

713
00:47:13,143 --> 00:47:14,300
She killed herself.

714
00:47:14,362 --> 00:47:17,050
She was heartbroken.
She left a suicide note.

715
00:47:19,601 --> 00:47:20,367
She died?

716
00:47:20,468 --> 00:47:21,687
She tried to kill herself.

717
00:47:40,760 --> 00:47:41,689
I was relieved

718
00:47:42,463 --> 00:47:43,220
What's wrong?

719
00:47:43,619 --> 00:47:44,674
It's nothing.

720
00:47:46,400 --> 00:47:47,970
Sawai.

721
00:47:49,244 --> 00:47:51,236
She was heartbroken.

722
00:47:52,720 --> 00:47:55,431
I know what it's like to die of rejection.

723
00:47:56,213 --> 00:47:58,299
I want to die, too.

724
00:47:59,845 --> 00:48:02,135
I was just kidding.

725
00:48:03,096 --> 00:48:04,573
That's what I thought at the time.

726
00:48:05,893 --> 00:48:07,424
Is she your wife?

727
00:48:10,307 --> 00:48:12,159
Congratulations.

728
00:48:12,596 --> 00:48:17,291
I came here by chance.

729
00:48:17,455 --> 00:48:19,120
What a coincidence.

730
00:48:19,729 --> 00:48:22,323
Come here,dad.

731
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:24,409
See you.

732
00:48:30,499 --> 00:48:32,640
What happened to you?

733
00:48:33,241 --> 00:48:35,577
I thought she was Asako.

734
00:48:35,663 --> 00:48:38,218
You don't have to worry about that.

735
00:48:38,296 --> 00:48:39,851
Look at the Beniko.
She is fine.

736
00:48:41,687 --> 00:48:42,460
Yeah.

737
00:48:43,179 --> 00:48:45,968
Promise me you won't worry about that anymore.

738
00:49:08,855 --> 00:49:10,012
You're gonna be late.

739
00:49:40,547 --> 00:49:42,008
Oshiyo, How are you?

740
00:49:42,336 --> 00:49:44,946
I'm fine.
I'm very busy.

741
00:49:45,547 --> 00:49:48,016
Oh, of course I'm having fun.

742
00:49:48,493 --> 00:49:51,618
How much one of your eggs?

743
00:49:51,883 --> 00:49:54,047
Egg?
Just a minute.

744
00:49:54,422 --> 00:49:56,626
Mom, how much is one egg around here?

745
00:49:56,727 --> 00:49:57,266
Egg?

746
00:50:00,055 --> 00:50:02,422
How much is one egg around here?

747
00:50:03,133 --> 00:50:06,352
Egg?
about 14 yen.

748
00:50:06,547 --> 00:50:08,180
13yen.

749
00:50:09,701 --> 00:50:11,099
It's 13yen.

750
00:50:11,490 --> 00:50:13,412
Thirteen yen?
Wow, that's expensive!

751
00:50:13,779 --> 00:50:16,552
I found a store that sells four for 50 yen

752
00:50:17,763 --> 00:50:18,701
I go there every day!

753
00:50:19,185 --> 00:50:22,021
Why so many eggs?
Okay, I get it.

754
00:50:23,818 --> 00:50:25,935
You're newlyweds, so you drink every day?

755
00:50:26,482 --> 00:50:29,053
I use eggs in many ways. Boil them, fry them...

756
00:50:29,474 --> 00:50:34,053
He has a lot of ingredients these days, so I'm trying to feed him nutritious food.

757
00:50:38,381 --> 00:50:40,826
Excuse me.

758
00:50:43,959 --> 00:50:46,170
How is Kasumi?

759
00:50:46,748 --> 00:50:47,936
She's fine.

760
00:50:48,865 --> 00:50:55,279
Would you like to have a party with us this Christmas?

761
00:50:55,514 --> 00:50:56,482
That's good.

762
00:50:56,725 --> 00:50:58,537
Try talking to her about it.

763
00:50:59,154 --> 00:51:00,607
I think she'll be happy.

764
00:51:00,811 --> 00:51:02,545
Sorry to bother you.

765
00:51:09,455 --> 00:51:13,502
Salt and pepper to taste.

766
00:51:22,999 --> 00:51:25,569
He came back too early.

767
00:51:25,976 --> 00:51:26,960
Welcome back.

768
00:51:30,880 --> 00:51:31,935
Kei-chan is not here?

769
00:51:33,966 --> 00:51:34,833
Who are you?

770
00:51:35,130 --> 00:51:36,966
Tell him I am Asako.

771
00:51:43,098 --> 00:51:44,934
I'll wait for him.

772
00:52:01,043 --> 00:52:05,254
They say a thief is more than a victim in that he's full of fear.

773
00:52:05,715 --> 00:52:07,473
I must stay strong.

774
00:52:09,387 --> 00:52:11,762
I'll turn on the stove.Take off your coat.

775
00:52:33,094 --> 00:52:35,344
Please, read this.

776
00:52:41,274 --> 00:52:43,563
You got married last month?

777
00:52:44,938 --> 00:52:46,587
You don't have to answer if you don't want to.

778
00:52:47,563 --> 00:52:49,446
You did nothing wrong.

779
00:52:52,436 --> 00:52:53,045
Where are you going?

780
00:52:53,514 --> 00:52:56,959
I'll go get the laundry.
I'll have to ask you for the permission?

781
00:53:37,568 --> 00:53:38,825
Welcome back.

782
00:53:39,348 --> 00:53:40,325
Why did you let her in the house?

783
00:53:40,396 --> 00:53:42,904
She forced her way into the house.

784
00:53:43,630 --> 00:53:47,794
I'm going to make pork stew tonight, so please let me know after you talk to her.

785
00:53:56,610 --> 00:53:57,688
Why did you come?

786
00:53:57,805 --> 00:53:58,876
I wanted to make sure.

787
00:53:59,251 --> 00:54:02,266
I was in shock.
I couldn't sleep.

788
00:54:02,626 --> 00:54:03,891
I'm sorry.

789
00:54:04,126 --> 00:54:06,360
You're a coward.

790
00:54:06,462 --> 00:54:10,008
You should have gotten married after you told me.

791
00:54:10,196 --> 00:54:13,415
You threatened me with death.

792
00:54:13,813 --> 00:54:14,782
You bastard!

793
00:54:15,055 --> 00:54:16,180
What do you want me to do?

794
00:54:16,844 --> 00:54:17,813
 What are you looking at?

795
00:54:18,298 --> 00:54:21,626
There's nothing to be done.
I had a glimmer of hope before I came here.

796
00:54:22,657 --> 00:54:27,048
I feel better now that I'm here.
And now that I've met you...

797
00:54:28,337 --> 00:54:29,032
Are you leaving?

798
00:54:29,368 --> 00:54:31,282
Are you leaving?

799
00:54:32,048 --> 00:54:33,102
I'm sorry to bother you.

800
00:54:54,562 --> 00:54:55,523
See you.

801
00:55:03,083 --> 00:55:06,755
I'm going back through that door.

802
00:55:06,865 --> 00:55:08,201
She's in danger.

803
00:55:11,247 --> 00:55:12,740
Close the door.

804
00:55:34,516 --> 00:55:36,414
I'm sorry to bother you.

805
00:55:38,172 --> 00:55:39,508
You should send her.

806
00:55:39,602 --> 00:55:40,133
You're right.

807
00:55:40,297 --> 00:55:40,977
Don't worry.

808
00:55:41,391 --> 00:55:42,891
I've had enough of your pretense of kindness.

809
00:55:43,195 --> 00:55:44,242
Don't say that.

810
00:55:44,563 --> 00:55:47,531
I'll be alright.
I'll go home alone. I'll live on my own.

811
00:55:48,352 --> 00:55:49,367
But.

812
00:55:49,392 --> 00:55:52,422
If you come, I'll scream on the stairs.

813
00:55:53,047 --> 00:55:57,008
I'll scream your name out loud.

814
00:55:59,166 --> 00:56:00,470
Is she ok?

815
00:56:01,174 --> 00:56:02,236
I'm sorry I bothered you.

816
00:56:03,330 --> 00:56:06,494
Don't say that.
Let's eat early.

817
00:56:11,398 --> 00:56:12,796
Are you starving?

818
00:56:13,179 --> 00:56:17,038
I don't feel like eating right now.

819
00:56:17,757 --> 00:56:19,062
You are too weak.

820
00:56:20,093 --> 00:56:21,085
What's this?

821
00:56:21,343 --> 00:56:24,140
Your sister brought me a Christmas present from the office today.

822
00:56:24,468 --> 00:56:25,202
This is for you.

823
00:56:25,227 --> 00:56:26,710
What's that?

824
00:56:29,438 --> 00:56:31,032
This is awesome.

825
00:56:35,586 --> 00:56:38,235
I wonder what she'll do now.

826
00:56:39,547 --> 00:56:41,055
That's what I was just thinking about.

827
00:56:41,860 --> 00:56:43,547
Maybe I should have sent her home after all.

828
00:56:44,321 --> 00:56:46,407
She's in danger.

829
00:56:46,563 --> 00:56:49,524
 I should've just grabbed her and taken her to the hospital.

830
00:56:50,235 --> 00:56:51,532
But she's not sick.

831
00:56:51,860 --> 00:56:52,454
So, the police?

832
00:56:53,258 --> 00:56:55,282
I wonder if the police will give her protection.

833
00:56:55,485 --> 00:56:57,157
Does she have any relatives?

834
00:56:58,187 --> 00:56:59,976
And it's none of my business.

835
00:57:00,499 --> 00:57:02,757
What should we do...

836
00:57:03,515 --> 00:57:04,616
I feel worry.

837
00:57:05,124 --> 00:57:06,523
Do you have any ideas?

838
00:57:14,288 --> 00:57:15,381
Excuse me.

839
00:57:16,670 --> 00:57:19,702
You really look like a wife.

840
00:57:19,795 --> 00:57:22,749
we have been waiting for you for a long time.

841
00:57:22,842 --> 00:57:24,467
There's so much to talk about !

842
00:57:24,616 --> 00:57:28,405
But I'll start with Kasumi's story.
Why did you call me?

843
00:57:28,569 --> 00:57:30,077
I'll tell you later.

844
00:57:30,631 --> 00:57:33,194
As a matter of fact, Asako was at our home the other day.

845
00:57:33,389 --> 00:57:35,108
She finally showed up.

846
00:57:37,834 --> 00:57:42,772
But I'm glad it didn't become a big problem.

847
00:57:43,147 --> 00:57:46,280
Not really.
I get nervous every morning when I read the paper.

848
00:57:46,366 --> 00:57:47,350
Why?

849
00:57:47,499 --> 00:57:49,670
I wonder why there's an article about Asako's suicide.

850
00:57:50,030 --> 00:57:51,866
You think too much.

851
00:57:53,428 --> 00:57:55,655
I want to hear your story.

852
00:57:56,131 --> 00:58:00,483
It's Christmas Eve tonight.
I'm thinking of having an all-nighter with Maki.

853
00:58:01,133 --> 00:58:01,992
all-nighter?

854
00:58:03,375 --> 00:58:06,203
I'm really into him.

855
00:58:06,890 --> 00:58:07,859
What do you mean?

856
00:58:10,562 --> 00:58:11,797
You can't sleep with him.

857
00:58:11,822 --> 00:58:13,047
It's ok.

858
00:58:13,148 --> 00:58:13,859
That's bad.

859
00:58:14,304 --> 00:58:16,984
Why?

860
00:58:17,383 --> 00:58:21,859
Actually. I never told you this, but...

861
00:58:22,297 --> 00:58:25,320
Don't be offended.

862
00:58:26,304 --> 00:58:29,453
Maki's been living with a woman for about a year.

863
00:58:29,968 --> 00:58:32,039
That's a lie.

864
00:58:32,578 --> 00:58:35,531
It's true.
The detective took full responsibility for the report

865
00:58:35,556 --> 00:58:39,484
You're a big talker, aren't you?
What right do you have to investigate Maki?

866
00:58:39,517 --> 00:58:40,757
Don't get me wrong.

867
00:58:40,782 --> 00:58:42,304
It's none of your business.

868
00:58:42,593 --> 00:58:46,234
If you have time to check on Maki-san, why don't you keep a closer eye on your own precious husband?

869
00:58:47,148 --> 00:58:49,828
What's wrong with Kei-chan?

870
00:58:50,195 --> 00:58:52,734
I'm appalled.
When did Kasumi become such an idiot?

871
00:58:54,524 --> 00:59:00,868
That Asako didn't know about your marriage until recently.
That's because Kei-chan acted like he was single.

872
00:59:01,087 --> 00:59:05,532
And the reason she didn't kill herself after you yelled at her...
Kei-chan talked her into getting back together with you.

873
00:59:06,087 --> 00:59:07,532
I don't think he would do that.

874
00:59:07,665 --> 00:59:08,696
You think so?

875
00:59:09,274 --> 00:59:10,009
Yeah.

876
00:59:10,524 --> 00:59:12,501
He has come home every day since we got married.

877
00:59:12,728 --> 00:59:16,798
How stupid can you be?
The other day Kasumi called and said he's been working late.

878
00:59:17,298 --> 00:59:22,368
Lately, lunchtime affairs are all the rage among office workers.

879
00:59:22,884 --> 00:59:25,571
You make him eat eggs every day and you feel stupid.

880
00:59:26,235 --> 00:59:32,548
Maki said your sister was very close to Kei-chan when she was single.

881
00:59:32,876 --> 00:59:36,095
You two are a man and a woman, so be careful.

882
00:59:36,462 --> 00:59:38,595
You never know, you might have enemies among your own people.

883
00:59:46,459 --> 00:59:47,139
You want some?

884
00:59:47,342 --> 00:59:48,482
No thanks.

885
00:59:48,920 --> 00:59:50,342
Just one cup.

886
00:59:50,367 --> 00:59:51,607
That's enough.

887
00:59:53,714 --> 00:59:55,066
You want some?

888
01:00:05,751 --> 01:00:10,110
You are very black-hearted.
I won't be fooled.

889
01:00:14,524 --> 01:00:18,649
I think it's strange to have a party outside on Christmas Eve.

890
01:00:19,063 --> 01:00:23,391
In America, Christmas Eve is a family affair.

891
01:00:24,501 --> 01:00:25,399
Please give me more wine.

892
01:00:25,532 --> 01:00:30,040
It's fine to celebrate at home. But if you drink too much, you won't get anywhere.

893
01:00:44,634 --> 01:00:46,181
I have to go.

894
01:00:46,408 --> 01:00:48,548
Take that.

895
01:00:50,166 --> 01:00:50,760
Take that.

896
01:00:50,900 --> 01:00:52,283
One for Kasumi.

897
01:00:54,400 --> 01:00:55,361
For Kasumi, too?

898
01:00:56,830 --> 01:01:01,580
Because I'm really sorry to Kasumi for doing this.

899
01:01:16,776 --> 01:01:18,776
Won't you dance?

900
01:01:19,487 --> 01:01:20,550
Let's dance.

901
01:01:21,253 --> 01:01:23,112
I don't want.

902
01:01:24,542 --> 01:01:25,182
What's wrong?

903
01:01:25,378 --> 01:01:26,768
Are you sick?

904
01:01:27,714 --> 01:01:29,018
Are you sick?

905
01:01:29,604 --> 01:01:31,221
I'm not.

906
01:01:32,885 --> 01:01:34,206
Anyway, let's play a record.

907
01:01:35,221 --> 01:01:35,987
I don't like it without music.

908
01:01:36,471 --> 01:01:38,495
Akiko, put on a record.

909
01:01:39,448 --> 01:01:41,667
I have a record in my room.

910
01:01:58,810 --> 01:02:01,685
Please think about it seriously.

911
01:02:28,953 --> 01:02:30,500
I don't know why he laughed.

912
01:02:31,453 --> 01:02:33,117
I don't like the idea of he laughing at hisself.

913
01:02:34,312 --> 01:02:37,680
I'm sure he's just trying to impress some other girl when I'm not looking.

914
01:02:43,476 --> 01:02:44,242
I'm off.

915
01:02:46,117 --> 01:02:48,132
I knew it. You misunderstood me, didn't you?

916
01:02:48,157 --> 01:02:48,835
Misunderstood what?

917
01:02:48,945 --> 01:02:50,179
Your sis worried about you.

918
01:02:50,453 --> 01:02:53,898
She said you were suspicious of us.
I told her that's not true.

919
01:02:54,320 --> 01:02:58,523
And she says, "You can't be so optimistic.
She said, "You've got to really think about it.

920
01:02:58,835 --> 01:03:02,593
And then you come down the stairs... and you put on a record.
Were you crying?

921
01:03:02,812 --> 01:03:04,273
You'll be late.

922
01:03:04,374 --> 01:03:05,687
Okay, bye.

923
01:03:08,101 --> 01:03:08,882
I'm off.

924
01:03:39,051 --> 01:03:39,824
Excuse me.

925
01:03:39,849 --> 01:03:43,871
This is the candy I forgot to give you last night.

926
01:03:44,590 --> 01:03:46,254
You scared me.

927
01:03:46,972 --> 01:03:48,566
Come in.

928
01:03:48,605 --> 01:03:52,715
I was told not to talk to you long.

929
01:03:53,918 --> 01:03:55,066
I get it.

930
01:03:57,191 --> 01:03:59,738
Your husband has been coming home late lately.

931
01:04:01,222 --> 01:04:01,839
Why?

932
01:04:01,917 --> 01:04:08,495
There are rumors that he has an affair with a woman at the bar.

933
01:04:10,852 --> 01:04:12,251
Is that true?

934
01:04:12,360 --> 01:04:17,454
Oops..
But I thought I'd better warn you.

935
01:04:18,883 --> 01:04:20,797
I'm leaving.

936
01:04:21,305 --> 01:04:25,118
Don't you dare tell your mother what you just said.

937
01:04:25,748 --> 01:04:27,068
I'm sorry to have bothered you.

938
01:04:52,026 --> 01:04:53,409
That's what I thought.

939
01:04:55,565 --> 01:04:56,807
There's a phone call for you.

940
01:04:57,026 --> 01:04:58,276
Thank you very much.

941
01:04:59,151 --> 01:05:00,807
Kasumi? It's me.

942
01:05:01,573 --> 01:05:03,401
I'm going to be home a little late today.

943
01:05:03,729 --> 01:05:06,706
You said you'd be home early.

944
01:05:07,120 --> 01:05:07,893
Why?

945
01:05:08,268 --> 01:05:11,174
Because I have to take care of something.

946
01:05:11,542 --> 01:05:14,034
What errands? It's not for the company, is it?

947
01:05:14,635 --> 01:05:15,956
What kind of errands?

948
01:05:16,127 --> 01:05:18,135
It's none of your business.

949
01:05:21,987 --> 01:05:24,619
Ok I get it...

950
01:05:34,523 --> 01:05:35,289
Who?

951
01:05:36,343 --> 01:05:37,132
It's me.

952
01:05:38,578 --> 01:05:39,460
KASUMI

953
01:05:41,257 --> 01:05:42,023
Come in.

954
01:05:49,927 --> 01:05:51,286
I just thought I'd stop by.

955
01:05:52,364 --> 01:05:54,442
Going on a trip or something?

956
01:05:56,356 --> 01:05:58,255
Yes, with Chieko.

957
01:05:59,848 --> 01:06:01,302
So Keiichi will be lonely.

958
01:06:02,333 --> 01:06:06,333
I'm currently working on this, so please wait a moment.

959
01:06:09,973 --> 01:06:14,591
I think he'd be happier without me.

960
01:06:19,791 --> 01:06:22,345
Am I intruding?

961
01:06:23,916 --> 01:06:24,595
Why?

962
01:06:25,025 --> 01:06:26,533
But you keep looking at your watch.

963
01:06:26,775 --> 01:06:30,736
No, it's time for the stock market broadcast.

964
01:06:30,892 --> 01:06:35,564
I bought my first stock yesterday.
I thought it might go down.

965
01:06:38,274 --> 01:06:39,532
I see.

966
01:06:48,881 --> 01:06:52,725
You have something to worry about?

967
01:06:55,537 --> 01:06:59,709
That's what I thought.
I knew you were crying last night.

968
01:07:00,545 --> 01:07:01,514
I was worried about you.

969
01:07:02,287 --> 01:07:04,694
I was doubting your relationship.

970
01:07:06,897 --> 01:07:11,967
I knew it.
It was hard for me.  Because I like you.

971
01:07:13,233 --> 01:07:14,459
I'm sorry.

972
01:07:16,725 --> 01:07:19,069
I'm glad we got it all straightened out.

973
01:07:20,287 --> 01:07:22,264
You know what?

974
01:07:24,577 --> 01:07:26,452
Kei-chan seems to be having an affair with someone.

975
01:07:27,647 --> 01:07:28,475
with who?

976
01:07:29,420 --> 01:07:32,709
With a bar girl.
Your bros saw them.

977
01:07:33,537 --> 01:07:36,389
Your bros said that last night?

978
01:07:38,295 --> 01:07:39,280
I can't believe it.

979
01:07:39,506 --> 01:07:44,272
What did your brother say about her?

980
01:07:44,913 --> 01:07:50,561
He said he sometimes saw them together at a bar in Ginza these days.

981
01:07:51,030 --> 01:07:52,053
What bar?

982
01:07:52,913 --> 01:07:53,905
I didn't ask that much.

983
01:07:53,930 --> 01:07:54,842
What's she like?

984
01:07:55,757 --> 01:07:57,303
I heard she had long hair.

985
01:07:58,866 --> 01:08:00,194
She must be Asako.

986
01:08:02,108 --> 01:08:05,616
Is she tall and thin?

987
01:08:05,780 --> 01:08:07,694
Yes.
Your brother said so too?

988
01:08:09,327 --> 01:08:10,303
No..

989
01:08:10,913 --> 01:08:12,608
So you saw her?

990
01:08:13,397 --> 01:08:14,038
Yes.

991
01:08:14,374 --> 01:08:15,444
When?
Where?

992
01:08:16,233 --> 01:08:21,428
I only saw them together in Ginza 10 days ago.

993
01:08:21,874 --> 01:08:24,233
That's what I thought.

994
01:08:26,014 --> 01:08:28,030
Asako's turned to be bar girl.

995
01:08:30,491 --> 01:08:31,663
Please don't hate me.

996
01:08:32,022 --> 01:08:38,374
I never thought I'd be able to live with you for so long.

997
01:08:39,428 --> 01:08:42,132
I played a strange role this time.

998
01:08:43,108 --> 01:08:46,186
I think you are lucky to have a friend like Sawai.

999
01:08:46,905 --> 01:08:47,702
Thank you very much.

1000
01:08:48,608 --> 01:08:49,194
I was sorry.

1001
01:08:50,116 --> 01:08:54,178
Never mind.
I told you I didn't care.

1002
01:09:10,776 --> 01:09:11,713
Welcome.

1003
01:09:14,730 --> 01:09:20,894
Ms. Asako, who used to work here, where is she working now?

1004
01:09:21,058 --> 01:09:25,027
She's  still working here.
Asako, you have a guest.

1005
01:09:28,651 --> 01:09:30,776
Oh Sawai's wife.

1006
01:09:32,713 --> 01:09:34,666
Are you going on a trip?

1007
01:09:35,009 --> 01:09:37,400
I have something to say to you.

1008
01:09:37,425 --> 01:09:42,994
I'm just about to go home too.
Let's have a coffee.

1009
01:09:43,533 --> 01:09:45,612
Hold on.

1010
01:09:54,010 --> 01:09:57,198
I did meet your husband 10 days ago.

1011
01:09:57,940 --> 01:10:03,940
We came to this coffee shop after work.
I had something to consult with him

1012
01:10:07,192 --> 01:10:08,527
What do you want to consult with me?

1013
01:10:08,752 --> 01:10:10,979
I'm thinking of getting married.

1014
01:10:11,352 --> 01:10:13,192
With who?

1015
01:10:14,177 --> 01:10:16,510
Mr. Kawakami, an architectural engineer.

1016
01:10:16,710 --> 01:10:21,630
He didn't get married until he was 35 because he was busy working on the dam.

1017
01:10:22,921 --> 01:10:24,375
He is a regular customer of my shop.

1018
01:10:25,195 --> 01:10:27,601
It's been 3 months since I met him.

1019
01:10:28,175 --> 01:10:30,689
At first I was dating him because I was lonely.

1020
01:10:31,228 --> 01:10:34,248
I went to your apartment the other day,right?

1021
01:10:35,029 --> 01:10:40,276
At that moment I felt you were no longer my concern.

1022
01:10:41,230 --> 01:10:44,490
After that, I started to understand Kawakami's charm.

1023
01:10:45,485 --> 01:10:48,678
So I decided to restart.

1024
01:10:49,275 --> 01:10:54,042
I'm thinking of telling him everything about you before I respond with his proposal.

1025
01:10:54,552 --> 01:10:55,785
About me?

1026
01:10:56,469 --> 01:10:58,756
I don't care but...

1027
01:10:59,359 --> 01:11:01,079
I think you should not tell him.

1028
01:11:01,181 --> 01:11:04,161
That's a common response.

1029
01:11:04,922 --> 01:11:07,668
But I don't think it should be hidden.

1030
01:11:07,925 --> 01:11:10,125
I want him to know my true feelings.

1031
01:11:10,927 --> 01:11:11,527
I know how you feel but..

1032
01:11:11,802 --> 01:11:13,055
What do you think?

1033
01:11:13,087 --> 01:11:14,722
I think you should not tell him...

1034
01:11:15,372 --> 01:11:17,978
I have no idea.

1035
01:11:18,085 --> 01:11:21,518
I have to reply to him soon.

1036
01:11:21,725 --> 01:11:22,998
It's too sudden.

1037
01:11:23,218 --> 01:11:30,477
I was very confused and decided to talk to you.

1038
01:11:30,882 --> 01:11:32,195
What do you think?

1039
01:11:33,142 --> 01:11:35,515
Oh my god..

1040
01:11:36,939 --> 01:11:37,586
Oh.

1041
01:11:39,734 --> 01:11:43,817
I couldn't wait for you to reply.

1042
01:11:44,530 --> 01:11:47,270
He’s My male friend,Sawai.

1043
01:11:48,055 --> 01:11:48,821
I'm Kawakami.

1044
01:11:48,908 --> 01:11:49,681
Nice to meet you.

1045
01:11:50,496 --> 01:11:51,489
I'm leaving.

1046
01:11:51,522 --> 01:11:52,968
Please stay here.

1047
01:11:53,069 --> 01:11:55,389
But I'm on the way working.

1048
01:11:56,163 --> 01:11:57,083
See you.

1049
01:12:03,155 --> 01:12:04,308
He looks nice.

1050
01:12:05,312 --> 01:12:08,652
I want to tell you something before I reply to you.

1051
01:12:09,298 --> 01:12:09,925
What?

1052
01:12:10,388 --> 01:12:12,735
About my past.

1053
01:12:12,760 --> 01:12:17,074
Hold on.
I think you should not tell me...

1054
01:12:17,875 --> 01:12:21,695
I'm not going to marry your past.

1055
01:12:22,115 --> 01:12:23,748
I'm going to marry you from now on.

1056
01:12:24,271 --> 01:12:29,238
You don't need to tell me about your past, and I don't need to listen.

1057
01:12:30,721 --> 01:12:33,548
I want to hear your reply about marriage.

1058
01:12:34,208 --> 01:12:35,035
Kawakami...

1059
01:12:45,074 --> 01:12:46,554
Oh I see.

1060
01:12:48,608 --> 01:12:50,901
He's so nice.

1061
01:12:51,283 --> 01:12:53,263
Yes he is.

1062
01:12:53,752 --> 01:12:56,172
He is the most wonderful man in the world.

1063
01:12:58,298 --> 01:12:59,272
What's wrong?

1064
01:13:00,986 --> 01:13:04,326
